<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{y}=-{49}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{7}{y}={81}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},{7}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{1}{y}=-{49}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}=-{49}-{\left({1}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{49}-{\left({1}{y}\right)}}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{\left(\frac{{-{49}-{\left({1}{y}\right)}}}{{7}}\right)}+{7}{y}={81}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{4}}{{7}}\cdot{\left(-{49}\right)}--\frac{{4}}{{7}}{\left({1}\right)}{y}+{7}{y}={81}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{28}-{\left({0.57142857142857}\right)}{y}+{7}{y}={81}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.57142857142857}{y}+{\left({7}\right)}{y}={81}-{28}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.57142857142857}{y}+{\left({7}\right)}{y}={53}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({0.57142857142857}+{\left({7}\right)}\right)}{y}={53}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7.5714285714286}{y}={53}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{53}}{{7.5714285714286}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={7}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{1}{\left({7}\right)}=-{49}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{\left({7}\right)}=-{49}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}=-{49}-{\left({7}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}=-{56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{56}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{8}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},{7}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
